relevanet: Only apply non-null Groovy Template properties.
When using the property defaults, this would leave the GroovyMarkupConfigurer bean with null values for autoIndentString, locale, and newLineString.
irrelevant: Previously, properties were always applied even when they had a null value.
The null values could cause problems at runtime, for example an NPE when Groovy Templates tries to call toString on the null newLineString.

relevanet: The count of remaining bytes is now initialized to the entry's uncompressed size.
The logic that closes the stream when remaining equals zero upon read or skip has been removed.
irrelevant: The available() method previously returned 0 initially and then negative values once some data had been read.
The available() method should return a positive value initially and decrease as data is read.
The condition for closing the stream was not reached before because remaining would become negative as soon as any data was read or skipped.
With the correct initialization of remaining, the condition is now reached and it results in test failures due to premature closure.
The javadoc of read and skip does not require the stream to be closed when the end of file is reached.

relevanet: GridFS is removed from MongoConnectionDetails.
Support for configuring GridFS through properties remains.
irrelevant: GridFS is a concept specific to Spring Data MongoDB.
MongoConnectionDetails provides general details for connecting to MongoDB, with or without Spring Data MongoDB.
GridFS does not belong on MongoConnectionDetails.

relevanet: This commit refactors ClassLoaderFiles to use a pre-computed, flattened map.
The ClassLoaderFilesResourcePatternResolver is updated to leverage this new, efficient structure:
getFile() and size() are improved from O(n) to O(1).
isDeleted() and getAdditionalResources() are improved from O(n*m) to O(m) by eliminating nested loops.
irrelevant: The resource resolver in DevTools can cause performance degradation during application restarts in large projects.
Key methods like isDeleted() and getAdditionalResources() rely on nested loops, leading to O(n*m) complexity.
Data consistency is maintained across all operations.
This optimization significantly improves restart performance with a minimal memory footprint, while preserving the existing API and exception handling behavior.

relevanet: Spring Boot now detects configuration formats based on the presence of ConfigurationFactory implementations
Reflection logic now uses the classloader that loaded Log4j Core, rather than the one associated with the Spring Boot context
The lookup now prioritizes configuration files specified via properties over automatically discovered ones
Files named in the form log4j2<contextName>.<extension> are now also supported
irrelevant: Log4j Core 3 has undergone significant modularization and no longer uses optional parser dependencies
These changes ensure compatibility with Log4j Core 3 while preserving support for Log4j Core 2

relevanet: This commit improves the Hazelcast health indicator to fail if the Lifecycle manager indicates that the instance is no longer running.
irrelevant: When the default Out-Of-Memory handler in Hazelcast detects a OOM error, and terminates Hazelcast, it does so on the node but not via the Hazelcast lifecycle manager.
The results is that it is still possible to successfully execute transactions in Hazelcast after this termination.
The health indicator should not report UP after Hazelcast has detected an OOM and terminated itself.

relevanet: Switch Logback's file logging charset to UTF-8
irrelevant: This commit aligns the file charset between Log4j2 and Logback
Prior to this commit, there was an inconsistency between the two: Log4j2 used UTF-8, while Logback used Charset.defaultCharset(), which is platform-dependent

relevanet: This PR rewrites ArchitectureCheckTests to support different sources and also adds functionality to configure the plugin.
With these changes, all tests now verify not only the checkArchitectureMain task but also checkArchitectureTest.
irrelevant: Polish ArchitectureCheckTests.
Prior to this commit, it wasn't possible to write a test to verify that a specific ArchRule applied only to a specific SourceSet.

relevanet: Update OutputCapture to fix a race condition that could occur due to the cache
irrelevant: Fix race condition in OutputCapture
Prior to this commit, when data was written whilst simultaneously being read, any subsequent reading of data might miss the last output

relevanet: If patterned_text length exceeds limit put in stored fields
if a log is long we stored it as a stored field rather than a doc value
If a message is over 8kb, we put it in a stored field
irrelevant: SortedSetDocValues can only hold 32kb per item
This puts a length limit on the arguments and template sizes used by patterned_text
Still parse a prefix of the field to create a template_id for sorting

relevanet: Standardizes how the Redact processor writes its `_ingest._redact._is_redacted` field to always create an intermediate object in the ingest metadata
PR also moves some commonly used ingest document test code to a place where it can be reused.
irrelevant: This protects users from not being able to see the field if the processor is run in flexible access pattern mode.

relevanet: Remove AlibabaCloudSearch*Action classes
Migrate Alibaba Senders to SenderExecutableAction
Consolidate redundant GoogleDiscoveryEngineRateLimitServiceSettings and GoogleVertexAiEmbeddingsRateLimitServiceSettings interfaces with GoogleVertexAiRateLimitServiceSettings
Rename fields on CustomRequestManager.RateLimitGrouping and AlibabaCloudSearchRequestManager.RateLimitGrouping
Add tests for AlibabaCloudSearchActionCreator
Migrate existing tests to AlibabaCloudSearchCompletionRequestManagerTests
Reserve square bracket syntax for ingest document flexible field access pattern
Adds validation to field path parsing to ensure that no square brackets are used in the path when flexible mode is enabled
irrelevant: We plan to introduce array indexing syntax to flexible mode in the future
To ensure that users do not make a habit of using this reserved syntax going forward, we are reserving it to ensure that it remains unused until it is supported

relevanet: Grant manage_threads to java.desktop for Tika
Produce a PolicyScope for excluded system modules
The construction of the service is raised out of the action module.
The instance is bound.
irrelevant: The MetadataIndexTemplateService used to be created as part of initializing the reserved project state handlers.
The instance was never bound.
A second instance was being created in the injector.
